Saved successfully to Postgres.


--- updatePage called at 2026-03-24T06:48:20.960Z ---
INPUT: {
  "pageId": "b5188c59-aaa9-4008-a453-2d38b44bb4db",
  "blockType": "blocks",
  "data": [
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "props": {
        "level": 1,
        "textColor": "blue"
      },
      "content": "Understanding Machine Learning"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "props": {
        "backgroundColor": "lightgray"
      },
      "content": "Machine Learning (ML) is a subset of artificial intelligence (AI) that enables systems to learn from data, identify patterns, and make decisions with minimal human intervention. It's all about teaching computers to learn from experience, much like humans do."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "props": {
        "level": 2,
        "textColor": "green"
      },
      "content": "How Does It Work?"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "props": {
        "backgroundColor": "lightyellow"
      },
      "content": "At its core, ML involves feeding large amounts of data into algorithms. These algorithms process the data, learn patterns, and build a model. This model can then be used to make predictions, classifications, or other data-driven decisions on new, unseen data."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "props": {
        "backgroundColor": "lightyellow"
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The learning process often involves "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "training",
          "styles": {
            "bold": true
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " the model on existing data, "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "validating",
          "styles": {
            "bold": true
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " its performance, and then "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "testing",
          "styles": {
            "bold": true
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " it with new data to ensure accuracy and generalization."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "props": {
        "level": 2,
        "textColor": "orange"
      },
      "content": "Key Types of Machine Learning"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "props": {
        "level": 3,
        "textColor": "purple"
      },
      "content": "1. Supervised Learning"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "props": {
        "backgroundColor": "lightblue"
      },
      "content": "This type of ML uses labeled datasets to train algorithms. The algorithm learns from input data and its corresponding correct output, eventually learning to map inputs to outputs. Examples include classification (e.g., spam detection) and regression (e.g., predicting house prices)."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "props": {
        "level": 3,
        "textColor": "purple"
      },
      "content": "2. Unsupervised Learning"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "props": {
        "backgroundColor": "lightgreen"
      },
      "content": "Here, algorithms work with unlabeled data to find hidden patterns or intrinsic structures within the data. It's used for tasks like clustering (e.g., customer segmentation) and dimensionality reduction (e.g., simplifying complex datasets)."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "props": {
        "level": 3,
        "textColor": "purple"
      },
      "content": "3. Reinforcement Learning"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "props": {
        "backgroundColor": "lightcoral"
      },
      "content": "In reinforcement learning, an agent learns to make decisions by performing actions in an environment and receiving rewards or penalties. The goal is to maximize the cumulative reward over time. It's often used in robotics, gaming, and autonomous systems."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "props": {
        "level": 2,
        "textColor": "red"
      },
      "content": "Common Applications"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "props": {
        "backgroundColor": "lightpink"
      },
      "content": "Machine Learning is transforming various industries. Some prominent applications include:"
    },
    {
      "type": "bulletListItem",
      "props": {
        "backgroundColor": "lightpink"
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "Image Recognition",
          "styles": {
            "bold": true
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": ": Identifying objects, people, or places in images."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "bulletListItem",
      "props": {
        "backgroundColor": "lightpink"
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "Natural Language Processing (NLP)",
          "styles": {
            "bold": true
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": ": Understanding and generating human language, like in chatbots or translation services."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "bulletListItem",
      "props": {
        "backgroundColor": "lightpink"
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "Recommendation Systems",
          "styles": {
            "bold": true
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": ": Suggesting products or content based on user preferences (e.g., Netflix, Amazon)."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "bulletListItem",
      "props": {
        "backgroundColor": "lightpink"
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
