INPUT: {
  "pageId": "970d71a6-4d6e-482a-8457-68c2c80e6562",
  "blockType": "text",
  "data": "This document outlines the **Arvyax Full Stack Internship Assignment** to build a **Secure Wellness Session Platform** with authentication, drafting, and auto-save capabilities.\n\n**Objective:**\nThe goal is to design and implement a full-stack application where users can:\n*   Securely register and log in.\n*   View public wellness sessions.\n*   Draft, auto-save, and publish their own custom sessions.\n\n**Preferred Tech Stack:**\n*   **Frontend:** React.js (or Vue/Angular/Next.js)\n*   **Backend:** Node.js + Express (or Django/Flask)\n*   **Database:** MongoDB (Atlas preferred)\n*   **Authentication:** JWT (jsonwebtoken + bcrypt)\n*   **Deployment (Bonus):** Render, Railway, Netlify, or Vercel\n\n**Core Features to Implement:**\n\n1.  **Authentication:**\n    *   `POST /register` for user creation (with hashed passwords).\n    *   `POST /login` to obtain a JWT token.\n    *   Secure storage of JWT on the frontend.\n    *   JWT middleware for protecting backend routes.\n\n2.  **Session Management API (Backend Routes):**\n    *   `GET /sessions`: Retrieve public wellness sessions.\n    *   `GET /my-sessions`: View a user's own sessions (draft and published).\n    *   `GET /my-sessions/:id`: View a single user-owned session.\n    *   `POST /my-sessions/save-draft`: Save or update a session as a draft.\n    *   `POST /my-sessions/publish`: Publish a drafted session.\n\n3.  **Frontend Pages:**\n    *   Login / Register forms.\n    *   Dashboard to view published sessions.\n    *   \"My Sessions\" page to view and edit user's own sessions.\n    *   Session Editor form including fields for Title, Tags, JSON file URL, \"Save as Draft\" / \"Publish\" buttons, and an optional auto-save feature (after 5s of inactivity).\n\n**Database Schemas:**\n*   **User:** `id`, `email`, `password hash`, `created_at`.\n*   **Session:** `_id`, `user_id`, `title`, `tags`, `json_file_url`, `status` (\"draft\" | \"published\"), `created_at`, `updated_at`.\n\n**Bonus Features (Optional, but Preferred):**\n*   Auto-save feedback (e.g., toast message).\n*   Fully functional logout.\n*   Responsive UI.\n*   Deployed demo of both frontend and backend.\n\n**Evaluation Criteria:**\nThe assignment will be evaluated on backend implementation (auth, JWT, API design), frontend (form handling, protected routes, UI), database schema, code quality (structure, naming, comments), system thinking, and bonus features.\n\n**Deliverables:**\n*   A GitHub repository with separate `/backend` (Node+Mongo+Express) and `/frontend` (React/Vue/etc.) folders.\n*   A `README.md` file containing setup instructions and API documentation, with an optional link to a live demo.\n*   An `.env.example` file listing required environment variables.\n\n**Estimated Effort:** 3-5 days, with an emphasis on quality and core functionality."
}
